com.observability.modeling.probe.descriptor

Interface DescriptorParser

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DescriptorParserImpl

    public interface DescriptorParser
    Parses the descriptors in a given directory and converts them to a manageable entity hierarchy. This object hierarchy can be used to create EMF semantic elements when initializing the model. This code is used when the modeler wants to create a model of the system. An EMF DbType entity would be created for each descriptor file present, a descriptor file is recognized by the .descriptor extension. When a cluster is associated with a DbType, all the machines created inside that cluster would automatically get the parameters denoted by the \@machine tag in the descriptor file. A more detailed description of the descriptor file can be found at https://github.com/observability/obs-prototype/wiki/Descriptor-File-Format
    Author:
    Caglayan "Gem" Gemici, Varun Saravagi
    See Also:
    DbType}, Parameter}, @see {@link ElementTag} Intermediate entities are used to ensure decoupling with EMF generated entities.
